sp.p:
No Sir, 'tis you that will repent it, I charge you in the King's Name to assist
      me in finding of my Daughter—Besure you leave no Part of the House unsearch'd;
      come, follow me.

Ay, well, thou art a good natur'd Fellow that is the Truth on't—Come then we'll
      to the Tavern, and sign and seal this Minute, Oh Felix be careful of
      thy self, or thou wilt break my Heart;

So now for the Colonel. (Goes to the Chamber Door.)
      Hist, hist Colonel. (Colonel peeping.
      )
